---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Publications - Yonatan N. Degefu">
  <div class="publications-container">
    <h1>Publications</h1>

    <p class="intro">
      You can also find my articles on <a href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=POp9Bk4AAAAJ&hl=en" target="_blank">Google Scholar</a>.
    </p>

    <section class="publications-section">
      <h2>Preprints</h2>

      <div class="publication">
        <h3>Cell state plasticity emerging from co-regulated, competitive, and configurable interactions, within the AP-1 network</h3>
        <p class="authors"><strong>Degefu YN</strong>, Bujnowska M, Baumann DG, Fallahi-Sichani M</p>
        <p class="venue"><em>bioRxiv [Preprint]</em>, 2025</p>
        <p class="description">
          Developed a mechanistic modeling framework revealing how AP-1 transcription factor dynamics drive cellular plasticity in melanoma through competitive and configurable network interactions.
        </p>
        <div class="pub-links">
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.1101/2025.11.06.686987" class="pub-link" target="_blank">Preprint</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="publications-section">
      <h2>Journal Articles</h2>

      <div class="publication">
        <h3>Novel synergies and isolate specificities in the drug interaction landscape of Mycobacterium abscessus</h3>
        <p class="authors">Van N, <strong>Degefu YN</strong>, Leus PA, Larkins-Ford J, Klickstein J, Maurer FP, et al.</p>
        <p class="venue"><em>Antimicrobial Agents and Chemotherapy</em>, 2023; 67(7):e00090-23</p>
        <p class="description">
          Systematically mapped drug interaction landscapes revealing novel synergies and isolate-specific drug responses in M. abscessus.
        </p>
        <div class="pub-links">
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.1128/aac.00090-23" class="pub-link" target="_blank">Paper</a>
          <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37278639/" class="pub-link" target="_blank">PubMed</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="publication">
        <h3>Design principles to assemble drug combinations for effective tuberculosis therapy using interpretable pairwise drug response measurements</h3>
        <p class="authors">Larkins-Ford J#, <strong>Degefu YN#</strong>, Van N, Sokolov A, Aldridge BB</p>
        <p class="venue"><em>Cell Reports Medicine</em>, 2022; 3(9):100737</p>
        <p class="description">
          Established design principles for assembling effective multi-drug TB regimens from pairwise interaction measurements, enabling rational combination therapy design.
        </p>
        <div class="pub-links">
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.xcrm.2022.100737" class="pub-link" target="_blank">Paper</a>
          <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/36084643/" class="pub-link" target="_blank">PubMed</a>
        </div>
        <p class="note"># Co-first author</p>
      </div>

      <div class="publication">
        <h3>C25-modified rifamycin derivatives with improved activity against Mycobacterium abscessus</h3>
        <p class="authors">Paulowski L, Beckham KSH, Johansen MD, Berneking L, Van N, <strong>Degefu YN</strong>, Staack S, et al.</p>
        <p class="venue"><em>PNAS Nexus</em>, 2022; 1(4):pgac130</p>
        <p class="description">
          Identified and characterized C25-modified rifamycin derivatives showing enhanced activity against M. abscessus.
        </p>
        <div class="pub-links">
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.1093/pnasnexus/pgac130" class="pub-link" target="_blank">Paper</a>
          <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/36714853/" class="pub-link" target="_blank">PubMed</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="publication">
        <h3>Systematic measurement of combination-drug landscapes to predict in vivo treatment outcomes for tuberculosis</h3>
        <p class="authors">Larkins-Ford J, Greenstein T, Van N, <strong>Degefu YN</strong>, Olson MC, Sokolov A, Aldridge BB</p>
        <p class="venue"><em>Cell Systems</em>, 2021; 12(11):1046-1063.e7</p>
        <p class="description">
          Developed systematic approach to measure drug combination landscapes and predict in vivo TB treatment outcomes using machine learning.
        </p>
        <div class="pub-links">
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.cels.2021.08.004" class="pub-link" target="_blank">Paper</a>
          <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34469743/" class="pub-link" target="_blank">PubMed</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="publication">
        <h3>Pharmacokinetics and Target Attainment of SQ109 in Plasma and Human-Like Tuberculosis Lesions in Rabbits</h3>
        <p class="authors">Egbelowo O, Sarathy JP, Gausi K, Zimmerman MD, Wang H, Wijnant GJ, Kaya F, Gengenbacher M, Van N, <strong>Degefu YN</strong>, Nacy C, et al.</p>
        <p class="venue"><em>Antimicrobial Agents and Chemotherapy</em>, 2021; 65(9):e0002421</p>
        <p class="description">
          Characterized pharmacokinetics and target attainment of SQ109 in TB lesions, informing optimal dosing strategies.
        </p>
        <div class="pub-links">
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.1128/AAC.00024-21" class="pub-link" target="_blank">Paper</a>
          <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34228540/" class="pub-link" target="_blank">PubMed</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="publications-section">
      <h2>Methods & Book Chapters</h2>

      <div class="publication">
        <h3>Efficient Measurement of Drug Interactions with DiaMOND (Diagonal Measurement of N-Way Drug Interactions)</h3>
        <p class="authors">Van N, <strong>Degefu YN</strong>, Aldridge BB</p>
        <p class="venue"><em>Methods in Molecular Biology</em>, 2021; 2314:703-713</p>
        <p class="description">
          Detailed protocol for using DiaMOND to efficiently measure multi-drug interactions in bacterial systems.
        </p>
        <div class="pub-links">
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-1-0716-1460-0_30" class="pub-link" target="_blank">Chapter</a>
          <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34235676/" class="pub-link" target="_blank">PubMed</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="stats">
      <h2>Publication Metrics</h2>
      <div class="stats-grid">
        <div class="stat-card">
          <h3>7</h3>
          <p>Total Publications</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <h3>1</h3>
          <p>Co-First Author</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <h3>Multiple</h3>
          <p>High-Impact Journals</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .publications-container {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: #00ff41;
    text-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 255, 65, 0.5);
  }

  h1::before {
    content: '# ';
  }

  .intro {
    color: #a0a0a0;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .intro a {
    color: #00ff41;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .intro a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .publications-section {
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    color: #00ff41;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #00ff41;
  }

  h2::before {
    content: '## ';
  }

  .publication {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #404040;
  }

  .publication:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .publication h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: #e0e0e0;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .authors {
    color: #a0a0a0;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .authors strong {
    color: #00ff41;
  }

  .venue {
    color: #00cc33;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .description {
    color: #c0c0c0;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .pub-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .pub-link {
    color: #00ff41;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: 0.4rem 0.8rem;
    border: 1px solid #00ff41;
    border-radius: 4px;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  .pub-link:hover {
    background-color: #00ff41;
    color: #0d0d0d;
    box-shadow: 0 0 15px rgba(0, 255, 65, 0.5);
  }

  .note {
    color: #00cc33;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .stats {
    margin-top: 4rem;
  }

  .stats-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .stat-card {
    background-color: #0d0d0d;
    border: 1px solid #00ff41;
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    text-align: center;
    transition: all 0.3s;
  }

  .stat-card:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 255, 65, 0.2);
  }

  .stat-card h3 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    color: #00ff41;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .stat-card p {
    color: #a0a0a0;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 1.4rem;
    }

    .publication h3 {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
    }

    .stats-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
